      "file_path": "controlloop/common/guard/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/guard/PipEngineGetStatus.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 230,
      "message": "preference would be to remove \"{}\".  Otherwise, change to: log.error(\"some message {}\", e.getMessage(), e).  The logging framework treats a final \"Exception\" object special and knows to log it and print a stack trace.  All other arguments are used to fill in \"{}\" place-holders while formatting the message.  In this case, I'm not sure what it puts there, but it's probably redundant.",
